{'contentformat': 'text/x-wiki', 'contentmodel': 'wikitext', '*': '{{PokémonPrevNext/Head|type=Fire |type2=Flying}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Pokémon|type=Fire |prevnum=662|prev=Fletchinder|nextnum=664|next=Scatterbug|roundleft=tl|roundright=tr}}\n{{PokémonPrevNext/Disambig|species=Talonflame}}\n|}\n{{Pokémon Infobox\n|name=Talonflame\n|jname=ファイアロー\n|jtranslit=Faiarō\n|tmname=Fiarrow\n|category=Scorching\n|typebox=1\n|type1=Fire\n|type2=Flying\n|abilityn=d\n|ability1=Flame Body\n|abilityd=Gale Wings\n|ndex=663\n|karea=Central\n|kdex=016\n|adex=160\n|height-ftin=3\'11"\n|height-m=1.2\n|weight-lbs=54.0\n|weight-kg=24.5\n|egggroupn=1\n|egggroup1=Flying\n|gendercode=127\n|eggcycles=15\n|evtotal=3\n|evsp=3\n|expyield=175\n|lv100exp=1,059,860\n|color=Red\n|catchrate=45\n|body=09\n|pokefordex=talonflame\n|generation=6\n|friendship=70\n}}\n\'\'\'Talonflame\'\'\' ([[List of Japanese Pokémon names|Japanese]]: \'\'\'ファイアロー\'\'\' \'\'Fiarrow\'\') is a dual-type {{2t|Fire|Flying}} {{OBP|Pokémon|species}} introduced in [[Generation VI]].\n\nIt [[Evolution|evolves]] from {{p|Fletchinder}} starting at [[level]] 35. It is the final form of {{p|Fletchling}}.\n\n==Biology==\nTalonflame is an avian Pokémon that closely resembles a falcon. Red-orange plumage covers is head, wings, and most of its chest and back before tapering off into a flame pattern. Its underside and hindquarters are gray and the tips of its long, pointed wings are black. Orange spots speckle its underside. Large yellow talons extend from the shaggy feathers on its legs. Talonflame has a pointed crest atop its head and black-and-yellow mask-like markings around its eyes. Its black beak is hooked with a yellow {{wp|Beak#Cere|cere}}. It also has long black tailfeathers marked with three yellow V-shapes. The tail ends in two points and has another feather sticking out of the base on each side, resembling of the {{wp|fletching}} on the end of an arrow.\n\nTalonflame feeds on other bird Pokémon, such as {{p|Wingull}} and {{p|Pikipek}}. It hunts by diving and attacking its prey with kicks before grasping them with its talons. When it dives, it can reach speeds of 310 miles per hour (500 kilometers per hour). It showers embers from the gaps in its feathers as it soars through the sky. Its wings are fireproof and have been used to make firefighter outfits in the past.\n\n==In the anime==\n===In the main series===\n[[File:Ash Talonflame.png|thumb|left|250px|Talonflame in the {{pkmn|anime}}]]\n\n====Major appearances====\n=====[[Ash\'s Talonflame]]=====\n{{Ash}}\'s Fletchinder evolved into Talonflame in \'\'[[XY086|A Legendary Photo Op!]]\'\' while protecting him and {{ashfr}} from a {{p|Moltres}}.\n\n=====Other=====\nTalonflame debuted in \'\'[[XY036|Battles in the Sky!]]\'\', under the ownership of [[Moria]]. She used it in a [[Sky Battle]] against a {{tc|Sky Trainer}}\'s {{p|Skarmory}} and won. Later, it beat [[Ash\'s Hawlucha]] before having a battle against {{AP|Fletchling}}; during this battle, it lost when Fletchling evolved into {{p|Fletchinder}}.\n\nA Talonflame appeared during a flashback in \'\'[[XYS05|The Legend of X, Y, and Z!]]\'\', under the ownership of {{OBP|Jan|XYS05}}. When Jan came across {{p|Yveltal}}, Talonflame was sent out to attack it, only to be turned to stone by {{m|Oblivion Wing}}.\n\n====Minor appearances====\nA {{pkmn|Trainer}}\'s Talonflame appeared in \'\'[[SM129|Battle Royal 151!]]\'\', where it competed in the [[Battle Royal]] preliminary round of the [[Manalo Conference]] but was defeated by [[Gladion\'s Silvally]].\n\n====Pokédex entries====\n{{Animedexheader|Kalos}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY036|Talonflame|Ash\'s Pokédex|Talonflame, the Scorching Pokémon and the final evolved form of {{p|Fletchling}}. Talonflame can swoop at incredible speeds when attacking. During intense battles, its wings give off showers of {{m|ember}}s as it flies.}}\n{{Animedexbody|XY086|Talonflame|Ash\'s Pokédex|Talonflame, the Scorching Pokémon and the evolved form of {{p|Fletchinder}}. During an intense battle, Talonflame expels embers from gaps between its feathers. It reaches speeds of more than {{tt|three-hundred miles per hour|480 km/h}} chasing prey.}}\n{{Animedexfooter/Pokémon|"XY"|Kalos}}\n\n===In Pokémon Generations===\n[[File:Honedge Lunatone Gyarados Talonflame Salamence PG.png|thumb|250px|Talonflame in [[Pokémon Generations]]]]\nA soldier\'s Talonflame appeared in \'\'[[PG18|The Redemption]]\'\', during a fantasy of a story from the past. It was one of the many Pokémon fighting in the great war of [[Kalos]] 3,000 years previously.\n{{-}}\n\n==In the manga==\n[[File:Malva Talonflame Adventures.png|thumb|200px|Talonflame in [[Pokémon Adventures]]]]\n===In the Let\'s Play the Pokémon Card Game XY! manga===\nTalonflame appeared as a card played by [[Manabu Kadoo|Manabu]].\n===In the [[Pokémon Adventures]] manga===\nA Talonflame appeared under the ownership of [[Malva]] in \'\'[[PAXY35|Yveltal Steals]]\'\'.\n\n==In the TCG==\n{{main|Talonflame (TCG)}}\n\n==Game data==\n===Pokédex entries===\n{{Dex/Header|type=fire|type2=flying}}\n{{Dex/NA|gen=VI}}\n{{Dex/Gen/2|gen=VI|reg1=Kalos|num1=016|label1=Central|reg2=Hoenn}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=X|t=FFF|entry=In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Y|entry=When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to {{tt|310 mph|500 km/h}}. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Omega Ruby|t=FFF|entry=In the fever of an exciting battle, it showers embers from the gaps between its feathers and takes to the air.}}\n{{Dex/Entry1|v=Alpha Sapphire|t=FFF|entry=When attacking prey, it can reach speeds of up to {{tt|310 mph|500 km/h}}. It finishes its prey off with a colossal kick.}}\n|}\n|}\n{{Dex/Gen/3|gen=VII|reg1=Alola|num1=160|label1={{gameabbrev7|SM}}:|reg2=Alola|num2=194|label2={{gameabbrev7|USUM}}:|reg3=Kanto}}\n{{Dex/NE|[[Pokémon: Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go, Eevee!|Let\'s Go, Pikachu! and Let\'s Go,